<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 611.529/171</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-10T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5408. Your 7127, September 7.<note n="1" xml:id="d328fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> Inform Foreign Office that Department has already
                            made investigation of domestic sulphur supplies which indicates that
                            latter are being utilized to full extent and are not capable of
                            increased production at present. United States in urgent need of
                            quantities of Spanish pyrites in addition thereto and no present
                            prospect of reduction of requirements therefor.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>